title: Nightly rustdoc ICE: `panicked at 'assertion failed: eps.array_windows().all(|[a, b]|\n        a.skip_binder().stable_cmp(self, &b.skip_binder()) !=\n `

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

### Error output

Whole output available at https://github.com/fedimint/fedimint/actions/runs/3233716428/jobs/5295926737

Just started happening in our CI on the one flow that doesn't have Rust locked via Nix, so I guess it must have just got introduced.

Please excuse very little information. I just want to report it timely, and I have move on to some other stuff for now.
